text: Marina Storozhenko (born 6 June 1985) is a Kazakhstani volleyball player. She played at the 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2012 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup, 2013 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2014 Asian Games, 2014 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for VC Zhetysu. == References == == Other websites == * Kazakhstan's libero previews FIVB Grand Prix Group 3 Finals Volleyball World, Aug 15, 2014 Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Kazakhstani volleyball players
